article.description: — Kevion Nolan had a career-high 32 points as Jacksonville narrowly beat Kennesaw State 62-57 on Friday night in the first Atlantic Sun Conference matchup of the season for both teams.
article.headline: Nolan leads Jacksonville over Kennesaw State 62-57
article.linkText: Nolan leads Jacksonville over Kennesaw State 62-57
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- — Kevion Nolan had a career-high 32 points as Jacksonville narrowly beat Kennesaw State 62-57 on Friday night in the first Atlantic Sun Conference matchup of the season for both teams. Tyreese Davis had 10 points and seven rebounds for Jacksonville (7-4). Bryce Workman added eight rebounds and Mo Arnold had seven rebounds. Spencer Rodgers had 13 points for the Owls (3-6), who have now lost four games in a row. Brandon Stroud added 11 points and seven rebounds. Terrell Burden had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
